\begin_layout Subsubsection
Polarization mechanisms
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Since the density of 
\begin_inset Formula $^{3}He$
\end_inset

 is too low, the spin exchange optical pumping was used instead of direct
 optical pumping 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand cite
key "3HeTarget"

\end_inset

.
 The 
\begin_inset Formula $K-Rb$
\end_inset

 mixture is first polarized by optical pumping.
 Three diode lasers were installed to generate right circular light.
 The ground state of 
\begin_inset Formula $^{85}Rb\,5S_{1/2}$
\end_inset

 splits to 
\begin_inset Formula $F=2$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $F=3$
\end_inset

 hyperfine status with the nuclear spin 
\begin_inset Formula $I=\frac{5}{2}$
\end_inset

 and electron spin 
\begin_inset Formula $S=\frac{1}{2}$
\end_inset

.
 Each 
\begin_inset Formula $F$
\end_inset

 splits to 
